e girl on the right has blonde hair pulled back with a small clip and wears a pink shirt. The hot dog is held between them, loaded with ketchup. As they lean in, red ketchup drips onto the front of the striped shirt, leaving a clear vertical stain. The girls smile and laugh, looking at each other and at the messy hot dog.\n\nNext, two boys stand among large white waterfowl, likely geese or ducks, with a black-and-white bird visible on the right and a pond, greenery, and zoo rock formations in the background. One boy has dark hair and wears a green-and-white striped shirt; the other is blond, wears glasses, and has on a peach shirt. They jostle and wrestle playfully while the birds crowd the foreground. The blond boy grabs at the striped-shirt boy, and the two boys tumble downward behind the geese, ending up low to the ground as if they have fallen into dirt or mud.\n\nThe product is then presented in a darker, studio-like display. A clear measuring cup with a handle sits beside the Fresh Start bottle. The cup contains a mound of white detergent, with a visible “1/4” marking on the front of the cup. The bottle beside it again shows the Fresh Start label and additional small text indicating “1/4 cup” concentration. White on-screen text appears over the measuring cup reading “Extra Stain Fighters.” The amount of detergent shown is small compared with the cup’s size, emphasizing the quarter-cup measure.\n\nThe commercial returns to the bleachers packed with children. Many are seated shoulder to shoulder, talking, smiling, and looking around. A closer view centers on the boy in the pale yellow shirt from the drink spill scene, now smiling among other children. On-screen text at the bottom reads “Chocolate Milk Stains,” and a red A appears beside it. The children around him smile and look toward him, as if his stain category has received a grade.\n\nThe next close view returns to the two girls from the ketchup scene, seated among other children on the bleachers. They lean